title: Trump Calls For ‘Modernisation’ Of New START Nuclear Arms Treaty With Russia | 10 News
description: US President Donald Trump has called for the ‘modernisation’ of the New START nuclear weapons treaty with Russia, as the existing agreement expires this week.  Trump said in a Truth Social post on Thursday, that rather than extend it, “we should have our nuclear experts work on a new, improved, and modernised Treaty.”  The agreement, which caps the number of deployed nuclear warheads at 1,550 on each side, has sparked fears of a new nuclear arms race as there will be no limits on the American and Russian arsenals. title: Investigators Believe Savannah Guthrie’s Missing Mother Still Alive After DNA Confirmation | 10 News
description: Arizona investigators say they believe Nancy Guthrie, 84, is still alive five days after her suspected abduction from her Tucson-area home.   Sheriff Chris Nanos confirmed blood found at the house has been matched to Guthrie’s DNA, however, he did acknowledge that there is still no proof of life.   The Federal Bureau of Investigation is examining a ransom letter sent to media outlets, while a separate letter was ruled an imposter note and led to an arrest.   "To anyone who may be involved, do the right thing. This is an 84-year-old grandma," the FBI special agent in charge Heith Janke said. title: Ukraine POWs Return Home In Prisoner Swap With Russia | 10 News
description: 157 Ukrainians have returned home after being imprisoned in Russia as prisoners of war, some of whom have been in captivity since 2022.  The prisoner swap came as part of peace talks between Ukraine and Russia, as the two nations look for a solution to end their conflict, which has raged for four years.
